The newspaper reported that Combest later gave a different story to the FBI, saying that Tower and a group of friends _ not Tower alone _ had frequently consumed a bottle of scotch.  John W. Tower has acknowledged that he drank excessively in the 1970s, but says he has reduced his intake to wine with dinner. Rep. A congressional source was quoted as saying that Combest told the senators that Tower would drink as much as a full bottle of scotch two or three times a week. He was chairman of the Senate Armed Services Committee from 1981 through 1984. 